	id="Exa_CoordinateVectorONB">
	<texsupport href="../LinearAlgebraTeXSupport.xml"/>
	
	<title>Coordinate Vector with Respect to an ONB: Examples</title>
	
	<showme>
		<statement>
			<para>Let <latex>V</latex> be the subspace of <latex>\RNr[4]</latex> spanned by the orthonormal vectors</para>
			<computation>
				<left>\Vect{a}</left>
				<center>:=</center>
				<right>\tfrac{1}{3} (1,-2,0,2)</right>
				<left>\Vect{b}</left>
				<center>:=</center>
				<right>\tfrac{1}{3}(0,2,1,2)</right>
				<left>\Vect{c}</left>
				<center>:=</center>
				<right>\tfrac{1}{3} (2,0,2,-1)</right>
			</computation>
			<para>Given that <latex>\Vect{x} :=(-1,-8,-5,15)</latex> is in <latex>V</latex>, find its coordinate vector with respect to the ordered basis <latex>\EuScript{B}:= (\Vect{a} , \Vect{b} , \Vect{c} )</latex>.</para>
		</statement>
		<answer type="Solution">
			<para>We need to express <latex>\Vect{x}</latex> as a linear combination of <latex>\Vect{a}</latex>, <latex>\Vect{b}</latex>, and <latex>\Vect{c}</latex>; i.e.</para>
			<computation>
				<left>\Vect{x}</left>
				<center>=</center>
				<right>s \Vect{a} + t \Vect{b} + u \Vect{c}</right>
			</computation>
			<para>Given that <latex>\EuScript{B}</latex> is an ONB of <latex>V</latex>, we compute:</para>
			<computation>
				<left>s = \DotPr{ \Vect{x} }{ \Vect{a} }</left>
				<center>=</center>
				<right>15</right>
				<left>t = \DotPr{ \Vect{x} }{ \Vect{b} }</left>
				<center>=</center>
				<right>3</right>
				<left>u = \DotPr{ \Vect{x} }{ \Vect{c} }</left>
				<center>=</center>
				<right>-9</right>
			</computation>
			<para>Therefore the coordinate vector of <latex>\Vect{x}</latex> with respect to <latex>\EuScript{B}</latex> is</para>
			<computation>
				<left>\Vect{x}_{\EuScript{B}}</left>
				<center>=</center>
				<right>(15,3,-9)</right>
			</computation>
		</answer>
	</showme>
</showme.pack>